# UI Primitives Rules

Always follow these rules when suggesting or editing UI primitive components in this project.

## Class Merging

- **ALWAYS** use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for class merging
- `cn()` combines `clsx` and `tailwind-merge` for proper Tailwind class deduplication
- Example:
```tsx
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";

className={cn("base-classes", className)}
```

## Component Patterns

### forwardRef Pattern
- **ALWAYS** use `React.forwardRef` for all UI primitives that accept refs
- **ALWAYS** set `displayName` after component definition
- Example:
```tsx
const Button = React.forwardRef<HTMLButtonElement, ButtonProps>(
  ({ className, ...props }, ref) => {
    return <button ref={ref} className={cn(...)} {...props} />;
  }
);
Button.displayName = "Button";
```

### Variant System with CVA
- **ALWAYS** use `cva` (class-variance-authority) for variant-based components
- **ALWAYS** use `VariantProps<typeof componentVariants>` for prop types
- **ALWAYS** define `defaultVariants` in the cva config
- Example:
```tsx
import { cva, type VariantProps } from "class-variance-authority";

const buttonVariants = cva(
  "base-classes",
  {
    variants: {
      variant: {
        default: "...",
        destructive: "...",
      },
      size: {
        default: "...",
        sm: "...",
      },
    },
    defaultVariants: {
      variant: "default",
      size: "default",
    },
  }
);

export interface ButtonProps
  extends React.ButtonHTMLAttributes<HTMLButtonElement>,
    VariantProps<typeof buttonVariants> {}
```

### asChild Pattern (Radix UI)
- **ALWAYS** support `asChild` prop when wrapping Radix primitives
- Use `Slot` from `@radix-ui/react-slot` when `asChild={true}`
- Example:
```tsx
import { Slot } from "@radix-ui/react-slot";

const Button = React.forwardRef<HTMLButtonElement, ButtonProps>(
  ({ className, variant, size, asChild = false, ...props }, ref) => {
    const Comp = asChild ? Slot : "button";
    return (
      <Comp className={cn(buttonVariants({ variant, size, className }))} ref={ref} {...props} />
    );
  }
);
```

## Button Variants

### Standard Button (`button.tsx`)
- Variants: `default`, `destructive`, `outline`, `secondary`, `ghost`, `link`, `brand`
- Sizes: `default` (h-10 px-4 py-2), `sm` (h-9 px-3), `lg` (h-11 px-8), `icon` (h-10 w-10), `icon-sm` (h-8 w-8)
- Default: `variant="default"`, `size="default"`

### Button V2 (`button-v2.tsx`) - Enhanced Variants
- Variants: `default`, `destructive`, `outline`, `galaxy`, `gradient`, `secondary`, `secondary-gradient`, `ghost`, `link`
- Special variants:
  - `galaxy`: Border with glow effect, shadow transitions
  - `gradient`: Blue gradient (`from-[#B5EAFF] to-[#00BFFF]`) with hover scale and shimmer effect
  - `secondary-gradient`: Uses `background-gradient1` CSS variable
- Includes `logo`, `logoAlt`, `logoSize` props for branded buttons
- Uses `transform-gpu` and `active:scale-[0.98]` for smooth interactions

## Card Component

- **ALWAYS** use compound component pattern: `Card`, `CardHeader`, `CardTitle`, `CardDescription`, `CardContent`, `CardFooter`
- Base classes: `rounded-lg border bg-card text-card-foreground shadow-sm`
- Spacing: `CardHeader` uses `p-6` with `space-y-1.5`, `CardContent` uses `p-6 pt-0`
- Example:
```tsx
<Card>
  <CardHeader>
    <CardTitle>Title</CardTitle>
    <CardDescription>Description</CardDescription>
  </CardHeader>
  <CardContent>Content</CardContent>
  <CardFooter>Footer</CardFooter>
</Card>
```

## Input Component

- Base classes: `flex h-9 w-full rounded-md border border-input bg-transparent px-3 py-1 text-sm shadow-sm transition-colors`
- **ALWAYS** include: `focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-1 focus-visible:ring-ring`
- **ALWAYS** include: `disabled:cursor-not-allowed disabled:opacity-50`
- File input styles: `file:border-0 file:bg-transparent file:font-medium file:text-sm`
- Placeholder: `placeholder:text-muted-foreground`

## Badge Component

- Uses `cva` with variants: `default`, `secondary`, `destructive`, `outline`
- Base: `inline-flex items-center rounded-full border px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold`
- **ALWAYS** include focus styles: `focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-ring focus:ring-offset-2`

## Dialog Component (Radix UI)

- **ALWAYS** mark as `"use client"` (uses Radix primitives)
- Compound components: `Dialog`, `DialogTrigger`, `DialogContent`, `DialogHeader`, `DialogFooter`, `DialogTitle`, `DialogDescription`
- Overlay: `fixed inset-0 z-50 bg-black/80` with fade animations
- Content: `fixed top-[50%] left-[50%] z-50 grid w-full max-w-lg translate-x-[-50%] translate-y-[-50%]`
- **ALWAYS** include close button with `sr-only` text for accessibility

## Typography Component

- Uses `cva` with multiple variant dimensions:
  - `variant`: `h1`, `h2`, `h3`, `h4`, `h5`, `p`, `small`
  - `weight`: `normal`, `medium`, `semibold`, `bold`, `extrabold`, `black`
  - `align`: `left`, `center`, `right`
  - `color`: `primary`, `secondary`, `embossed`, `submerged`, `boosted`, `destructive`, `foreground`, `background`
  - `size`: `xs`, `sm`, `base`, `lg`, `xl`
  - `gradient`: boolean (uses `bg-gradient-to-r from-[#B5EAFF] to-[#00BFFF] bg-clip-text text-transparent`)
- Supports `as` prop for polymorphic component pattern
- Default: `variant="p"`, `weight="normal"`, `align="left"`, `color="foreground"`, `size="base"`, `gradient=false`

## Accessibility

- **ALWAYS** include `focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2` on interactive elements
- **ALWAYS** use `ring-offset-background` for ring offset
- **ALWAYS** include `disabled:pointer-events-none disabled:opacity-50` for disabled states
- **ALWAYS** use semantic HTML elements (button, input, etc.) instead of divs for interactive elements
- **ALWAYS** include `sr-only` text for icon-only buttons (e.g., Dialog close button)

## SVG Handling

- **ALWAYS** use `[&_svg]:pointer-events-none [&_svg]:size-4 [&_svg]:shrink-0` for SVG children in buttons
- SVG size defaults to `size-4` (16px)

## Spacing & Layout

- Use consistent spacing: `p-6` for card sections, `gap-2` for button icons, `space-y-1.5` for vertical spacing in headers
- Padding patterns: `px-3 py-1` (input), `px-4 py-2` (button default), `p-6` (card sections)

## Animation & Transitions

- **ALWAYS** use `transition-colors` for color changes
- Use `transition-all duration-300` for complex animations
- Button v2 uses `transform-gpu` and `active:scale-[0.98]` for smooth press effects
- Gradient buttons use `hover:scale-105` for interactive feedback
